title: Sketchbook Folio, "Five Heads, After the Antique", 1810–20
medium: Pen and brown ink, brush and dark brown wash over traces of black chalk on white laid paper
inscribed: in pen and brown ink at lower margin: 30 monu antichi Parigi
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of various donors
description: Five heads arranged on page. At upper section two female heads possibly of same sculpture, shown with elaborate coiffeurs. Central head in profile Egyptian. Male and female head at lower section, both in profile to left.
